like a hip start-up.

03:41.280 --> 03:42.781
Open floor plan.
No walls.

03:42.820 --> 03:45.311
It'll take us a week.

03:46.360 --> 03:47.918
We can do this.

03:50.360 --> 03:51.622
Hey.

03:54.630 --> 03:56.666
And when did this happen?

03:56.700 --> 03:59.635
Well, right now. The
prosecutor's mid-trial

03:59.670 --> 04:01.297
and he's pressuring Tomas

04:01.340 --> 04:03.501
to sign the snitch
visa before noon.

04:03.540 --> 04:06.532
I told Tomas to wait till
he spoke to a lawyer.

04:06.580 --> 04:07.706
That's your friend? Tomas?

04:07.740 --> 04:09.571
Yes. Tomas Ruiz.

04:09.610 --> 04:11.305
I knew him in school.

04:11.350 --> 04:13.910
And who does this prosecutor
want him to testify against?

04:13.950 --> 04:17.841
Lalo Hierra.

04:17.890 --> 04:19.517
Yes, I know.

04:19.560 --> 04:21.312
It's worrisome.

04:21.360 --> 04:23.658
Okay, let me talk
to my partners.

04:23.690 --> 04:25.783
We're just... starting out.

04:25.830 --> 04:27.627
Yes, I can see that.

04:27.660 --> 04:29.560
Are these just
temporary?

04:29.600 --> 04:30.828
They're gonna look great.

04:30.870 --> 04:33.395
Just give us a week.

04:33.440 --> 04:35.431
(truck beeping outside)

04:38.070 --> 04:39.799
ALICIA:
It's just

04:39.840 --> 04:42.570
consultation on a visa,
but she needs me now.

04:42.610 --> 04:44.077
